{
  "version": "2.0.0",
  "cells": [
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": [
        "### Couples GloGEM & GloGEMflow test ",
        "",
        "IDL notebook to test the functionality of GloGEMflow integrated within the GloGEM framework. The flow model is now coupled to the elevation dependent mass balance. GloGEM updates geometries on the basis of ice flow equations as opposed to the dhdt parametrization."
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": [
        "Compile input"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "; define data directory",
        "data_dir = '/Users/janoschbeer/Library/Mobile Documents/com~apple~CloudDocs/PhD/projects/GloGEM/results_flow_model/r6_monthly/CentralEurope/'",
        "fig_dir  = '/Users/janoschbeer/Library/Mobile Documents/com~apple~CloudDocs/PhD/projects/GloGEM/products/figs/dhdt_vs_flow/'",
        "",
        "; restore geometry data",
        "restore, file_expand_path(data_dir + 'geometry_01450.sav')",
        "",
        "; Extract RGI ID from file name",
        "file_name = 'geometry_01450.sav'",
        "rgi_id = strmid(file_name, 9, 5)",
        "",
        "; scenario = 'dhdt'",
        "scenario = 'flow'",
        "",
        "; Update all relevant array names:",
        "; thickness_dx, width_dx, surface_dx, distance_dx for horizontal grid",
        "; thickness_dz, width_dz, area_dz, surface_dz, distance_per_band_dz, elevation_dz for vertical grid"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "horizontal_data_dir = '/Users/janoschbeer/Library/Mobile Documents/com~apple~CloudDocs/PhD/projects/GloGEM/'",
        "restore, file_expand_path(horizontal_data_dir + 'horizontal_grid_inputs.sav')",
        "x = horizontal_grid_inputs.x",
        "sur_x_input = horizontal_grid_inputs.surface_dx",
        "width_x_input = horizontal_grid_inputs.width_dx",
        "th_x_input = horizontal_grid_inputs.thickness_dx",
        "bed_x_input = horizontal_grid_inputs.bed_x_input"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": [
        "n_elements(sur_x_input)",
        "; Plotting and diagnostics now use thickness_dx, width_dx, surface_dx, distance_dx, thickness_dz, width_dz, area_dz, surface_dz, distance_per_band_dz, elevation_dz"
      ],
      "metadata": {},
